nts of a given type.\n    24→  - `getProfitAndLoss(startDate?, endDate?)` — Returns revenue minus expenses for the period.\n    25→\n    26→## Known Issues\n    27→\n    28→Users have reported:\n    29→1. Trial balance doesn't balance in some scenarios\n    30→2. Account statements show wrong running balances\n    31→3. Split entries sometimes create unbalanced journal entries\n    32→4. Date filtering in statements is off-by-one\n    33→5. P&L calculation has sign errors\n    34→6. Currency mismatch validation isn't working\n    35→7. Duplicate account names aren't rejected\n    36→8. getBalance returns wrong sign for liability accounts\n    37→\n    38→## Validation\n    39→\n    40→```bash\n    41→npm test      # Run tests (32/40 passing currently)\n    42→npm run build # Should compile cleanly\n    43→npm run lint  # Should pass\n    44→```\n    45→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01NbkenkF5Xb4q2saeLGjSUw","session_id":"4cead605-a458-4ebf-a71c-bc8c17135ec0","uuid":"1975c91b-e0fe-466c-9215-76e8c0e287ef"}
